The CSO mimics the brood parasite attitude of cuckoos where the cuckoos put their eggs surreptitiously in the host birds’ nests. Fraudfully, the cuckoos try to empty the nests of the host birds out of their own eggs, keeping only the cuckoos’ eggs to enhance the hatching amount. The cuckoos implement a haphazard strategy to pick the host nest. Furthermore, the basic construction of CSO depends on three concepts, relying on which each cuckoo produces next solutions referring to (16) [118–120].16XPit+1=XPit+λ⊕Levy(ε)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
